  "texts": [
    "Meanwhile, self-supervised learning (Liu et al. 2021) derives labels from the data itself, allowing models to uncover inherent relationships within datasets, such as interactions between different flavor compounds, which leads to nuanced predictions regarding taste interactions.",
    "The integration of deep learning techniques has further revolutionized taste analysis by effectively managing complex datasets and identifying intricate patterns that traditional models might overlook; for instance, CNNs can analyze food images alongside their associated flavor profiles (Zeng et al. 2023), enriching our understanding of visual-taste relationships.",
    "The data collection for taste analysis merges traditional and modern methods.",
    "Descriptive analysis, utilizing trained sensory panels, contributes to evaluating systematic sensory profiles, while consumer testing methods gather feedback from untrained individuals using hedonic scales.",
    "Additionally, electronic tongues (e-tongues) (Tibaduiza et al. 2024) utilize sensor networks to measure electrochemical responses that mimic human taste perception, delivering quantitative data crucial for flavor analysis."
  ],
